/* 
-= here be shops =-
data format goes like this:

trader <unique_trader_key>, <greed_modifier>
{
item1, amount, custom_price(optional)
item2, amount 
...
}

all item prices, except for items with the custom_price set, are multiplied 
by greed_modifier. If there's none, greed_modifier is 1 by default.


 -= How to use shops in dialog =-
to call the shop in dialog, add [trade KEY] to the dialog reply.
example: in LANGUAGE - 
TXT_WALKER_207 = "Let me see what you have. [trade Vance]";
in the conversation you'll see only "Let me see what you have.". Press it -
and boom, you trade Vance. You can add "SecretVance"  shop with other stock
and trade it from another line in the dialog. THE POSSIBILITIES ARE ENLESS
*/

